\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no. No, he never paid us. Just perhaps a - tanner or something like that for - toffees, occasionally we used to have - I 
mean you could go and get a lot of things then for a penny - now - they want pounds don't they, not pennies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 What was your job when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh I went mould-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654199\charrsid15081468 running}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Which is what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Working in the potbank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Can you sort of describe it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Well it's like - they make cups and plates and all that and you have to - put the clay in and then take 'em off the side when they've made 'em and put 'em in a hot stove. Steam you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 This was the kind of job that boys and girls who had just left school would be given is it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no, they could, please theirselves, in different jobs. But it was mostly potbank work and pits you see. Pits. And potbank work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would it be a sort of job that you progressed from or might somebody carry on in mould running as long as they carried on in work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no, no, you progressed from it. See I progressed and then I - I was cup maker. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So this in a way was a fairly unskilled job to get you into pottery work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
I wasn't a skilled work - it wasn't a skilled job, you see you had to work yourself up but - people didn't always stop at mould running, they went to warehouses and - different places you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Can you remember how you got the job? Was it a potbank where your parents knew people who worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no, you just can go get a job any time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 There were enough jobs for this to happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 People tell me it was a question of because people had relatives who could speak for them that they got a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Oh sometimes, but I mean I got me own job. There wasn't a lot of work about at one time you know, but - and we had to work for less money and - we didn't have the facilities as we had - as they have today. I mean
 - at one time - the - there wasn't any jobs at all, there was a kind of mean test you know for - a long time. For - most men and women. There was a mean test like us - we were younger then, we were only children. And we don't remember much about - I reme
mber it, there being a mean test 'cos me brothers was on mean test. See, you - there wasn't much work. You had to take what you'd got and you had to do it. And work hard and all, not like they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 But in your case you left school and you got the job straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. You had to get one, your mother wouldn't let you be out of work. Not - had to - do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh - I think it was seven in the morning 'til - six at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 An eleven hour day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes, sometimes twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You'd get an hour for lunch would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 An hour for dinner. And half an hour for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would this be five days a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Six. Saturday mornings 'til dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would you get holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh we had no holidays with pay then. Used to get holidays but you lost - you didn't have holidays with pay then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 What were you paid when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh I can't remember that. Few shillings I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you think it was a fair wage that you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Well you couldn't get no more, they wouldn't pay you no more. I think about five shilling, at first, they didn't pay much wages 'cos when I was - when I was a young woman I think and I - and I first went down to me apprentice job I thin
k I only got two pound six, for six days - well, five and a half. I think when - I think when the war was on, 1914, we used to get thirty shilling - for carrying clay up two flights of steps and - me and - me and another girl. Well we were getting on then
. Young women. Getting on for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 When you were doing the mould running were you allowed to keep your wages or did you have to hand them over to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no, you had to give your mother - you got about threepence pocket money or sixpence. That was your lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 This was the accepted practice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. And you could do a lot with threepence or sixpence them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 And the money you gave your mum would just go into the family expenditure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 How did you get on with the people that you worked with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 All right with some of 'em. Used to have - bit of a barney sometimes - with 'em you know. They weren't bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you know most folk where you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh I knew 'em all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You went to a local place, so it wasn't walking in with a lot of strangers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No. No. I knew 'em all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 What about your employer, did you know the person who owned the potbank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you think he was a good employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 What did you feel about the work, did you dislike it or did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Well I didn't like every job I had, we used to - keep on flitting around, seeing what we could get and - didn't like all the jobs you know. But you had to have it whether you liked it or not. Weren't
 up to you to say what you like and what you didn't, you had to have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So really it was a question of getting a job in the potbank and once you were there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13654199\charrsid15081468 maneuvering}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  to get a job that suited you better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you work in this same potbank all the time until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Oh no, I had a - worked at different potbanks. And I worked at different potbanks since I've been married. Done all different jobs and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would this apprenticeship job be after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 1914. Oh yes,
 I did - that job most of me life but you see - in them days if they said to you like - will you go and do this you'd have to go - you'd go like perhaps working in another shop or - would you go and help somebody else out, see I done a lot of jobs. That's
 how they were, you didn't just - stick to one job, if the boss asked you to do anything you'd go and do it for him you see and - probably in the warehouse or - in the kilns, I've done lots of jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So really you were at the mercy of the person who was employing you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
No you wasn't, you could please yourself, but I mean they didn't like you to refuse them you know. Some wouldn't but I mean I did, I - I weren't bothered. If I didn't like it I wouldn't do it, and if I liked it I'd do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did people move around fairly easily then from one potbank to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. And from one house to another. You'd flit your furniture at night time and go in another house next day and - that's how it was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So really all your life you've worked in potbanks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 What would this apprenticeship you were talking about consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well making cups and - pudding basins and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Was this a thing that you had to sign indentures for, like a formal apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No, you just did it. Please yourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Were there any trade unions in potbanks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you belong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 What kind of activities would it go in for, was it sort of protection of wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654199\charrsid15081468 Well - they didn't really like - put in for rises like the
y do today, you'd have a rise probably sometimes and - but it was for keep the conditions of the work - the factories you see, chiefly, and to see that you was - fairly treated you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you take an active part in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Just paying your subscriptions and hoping that you wouldn't need to call on their services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well - I - I felt really as - as the em - the bosses were out to get all out of you, every 
drain of blood in your body they'd sweat out of you really. You see - and you couldn't just - down your tools like and - and - you'd got the sack right away if you - had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654199\charrsid15081468 sack}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 , do without you '-cos he can get somebody else. And you see, they - you was o
n strict hours, you was locked out if you wasn't there certain time. Gates locked and you wouldn't get on you see. You'd either have to stop off and he let you on at breakfast time or - or you'd have to go home for the day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you feel there was
 any division of interest among the workers, would there be some people who thought of themselves as craftsmen, who thought of themselves as being better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You were conscious of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. And - some of 'em try to make more than you
 and some of 'em would - try - you see the - it used to be a shortage of the stuff and some of 'em'd try and get more stuff than you would perhaps you see, oh yes, all that went on. 'Course you had to work for yourself, get your own, see. When you was an 
apprentice. The more you made the more money you got and the less you made the less you got see, so everybody was out for - what they could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would you say that moving from school into work changed your attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You continued to live with your parents after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You stayed there until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 They didn't treat you any differently when you were bringing in a wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Some people were allowed more latitude at night, they could come in later.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh we could - I had to be in at half past nine a week before I was married. Yes. No leaving the keys and letting yourselves
 in in them days, you'd got to be in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did your brothers and sisters treat you any differently, did they look on you with sort of respect now that you were earning money?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well they didn't bother really. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654199\charrsid15081468 
Used to have set-to's you know, little fights and didn't bother 'cos - they were all - you know, we were always out playing and - didn't bother. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
When you come home from work you got so much work to do at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 This still carried on once you were in work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No. Went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You still went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 How old would you be when Sunday school dropped off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh - now - I suppose I was pretty old you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 And you still went to chapel as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. It was the same chapel see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You're not a politically minded lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Early on you told me about how you spent your spare time when you were at school, was there any great di
fference once you'd started work, were you allowed to go to the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes, we used to go pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 This was a change from when you were at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh aye, yes, we could go pictures when we went school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You'd come home from work, you'd have a certain amount of chores to do in the house, and then you could spend your time as you wanted?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Well we went with lads, we used to go out with lads and - knock around. Oh well, we used to have lads, used to play with lads. We were told y
ou couldn't do this and we couldn't do that, but we used to go off you know and - but - we weren't allowed out like late or anything like that, we had to be in. Or we had to know - they had to know where we were going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would they expect to know who you were with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh well you see we used to play with everybody around, everybody played with one another you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So it would be local friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you make any new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well they were mostly all neighbours y
ou know. We didn't - bother going off, we used to - go with the - neighbours children and the same neighbours where we lived round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So really it was a continuation of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well I don't think I made any special friends, if I fell out with one I'd go with somebody else and that's how we used to carry - go on.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You married after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 1919 I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did your mother think of herself as belonging to any particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 But you think she would say she was working class if she was asked?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well her is working - her was working class woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Why do you think she'd describe herself as a working class woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well because her
 had to work hard for a living, her used to take washing in and - look after us and - her used to wash for - other people and - her'd do anything for other people so I mean you are working class aren't you. One person was no different than another in them
 days to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
At this time would you think it was possible for somebody to move from the working class to being sort of middle class, or did you think that people were sort of born into one group and they more or less stayed in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no, there were different classes of people. I mean - one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 If you were born working class was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654199\charrsid15081468 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  possible to move to another class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes. I mean people used to work theirselves up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you know anybody who managed to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well I mean
 there's - meself really, I think a lot of people - worked theirselves up and made their money in the war, when the war was on, they didn't have anything that people like - didn't have a lot before the war, I think it was the war as made some - a lot of p
eople you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Oh yes, me grandma was a real lady. She was very nice person. And - and there were lot's of nice people. But me grandmother was - me father's mother was a lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Why was she described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Well, she was - she was like - I can remember her, she was old when I can remember her, but - like - she was a lady and - and - in my - my estimation, 'cos - you see she was very proud person, and ver
y nice, and - we used to go and see her Sunday mornings you know and you would have to - behave and - know your manners you know and that you see and - she was, she was a nice lady, me grandmother. But I don't know anything about me mother's parents you s
ee. Don't remember them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So really you would judge a real lady as somebody who behaved well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. And she was very refined lady, she was nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Do you ever remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh My God they w
ere never away, policemen. Never away from where we lived, policemen weren't. They were it in them days you know. On - and I've seen 'em knock the policeman's helmet off and - hit the policeman, oh policemen were always around. Didn't have to fetch 'em, t
hey were there. Them days you know there was scrapping, fighting and - women fighting, all sorts, they wouldn't put up with what they put up with today with 'em. I'll tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 How did you look on the policemen as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh well, I mean, we were frightened of policemen you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would your mother threaten you with the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 But you looked on the police as sort of guardians of order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well they were because in them days it was terrible you know, they were - and -
 as I say they were always - round, they weren't - you didn't have to ring 'em or fetch 'em, they were always round you know, coming round. Not in police cars neither, used to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Somebody told me policemen didn't come singly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No. Come in grou
ps. Yes. Sometimes policemen daren't come down. Used to be - they didn't bother in them days. Life's too easy today for 'em, I've - I was talking to a fellow yesterday, he used to play football up at Stoke and he said, he says, I'd rather have the days - 
t
he olden days down the Old Nook. I says, and me, I've said that many times. I would. Because everybody was more sociable, they aren't selfish and spiteful as they are today, that's what - makes the worked same as it is. We're spiteful people and greedy pe
ople.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 How do you think policemen treated people then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh well, if they were rough the policeman could be rough you know. Didn't get away with much you know you couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 But had you been in trouble would you have gone to the police fairly happily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well I wouldn't - no, I - we used to be frightened of policemen. Police come you was off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Can you tell me about the gambling in the streets then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh used to toss - coins up in the street like, you know, for money. Well then there us
ed to be - oh, crowds of them and then sometimes police'd come and he'd run 'em and - they'd run in anybody's house and - if you got your dinner there he'd sit down and eat your dinner 'til police had gone see, thinking police'd - think they lived there a
nd then they'd - sometimes the police'd catch a few of 'em and cart 'em off down the cells. Sunday afternoons and - used to be regular game Sunday afternoons and Saturdays, tossing and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 This would be mostly the fathers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes, men you know, not women. Card play for money you know, they used to play and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 And this would go in the streets outside houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 In the street, yes, street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Probably with somebody keeping watch for the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. Somebody keeping watch and then he -
 give them the wire when police are coming then they'd all run off. Some'd be caught you know. Some wouldn't. Oh that used to be a regular game. And then they'd have a fight - among theirselves and - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Would this be over who had won?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes, who won and who didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So you felt there was quite a lot of gambling going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Oh there was. Used to gamble. Well there's a lot today aren't there. But there was no bookies places like there is here. Like there is now. It's all gamble, and bingo, 
you'd no bingo nor nothing of that you know. They used to back horses and toss - for money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 And your dad joined in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh I don't ever remember me father tossing. But me father used to back horses. Lot of horses, 'cos he used to be a - what th
ey called a bookie's runner. Take bets for the bookie you know. He used to back a lot of horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 He could combine this with his other job in fact couldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did being a fishmonger run in the family or was this something he'd started himself, was his dad a fishmonger?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 I can't remember his dad. No, he started hisself up. Can't ever remember - his father. Nor me mother's parents either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh used to come every Monday for rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 How did your mother manage, was she able to pay the rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Sometime - oh well, if her wanted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654199\charrsid15081468 to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 miss it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  her'd miss it. Then I - I've seen her - I've seen the men and women even run the }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468 rent man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  off the street, not pay him. Aye. They used to hide theirselves if they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468 didn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
 want paying the rent. Tell the rent man I'm not in, or - they'd lock theirselves in, lock the doors and - I mean, you could go and get a house any time then. You didn't pay your rent you could g
o and get another house and - if you had the bums as took your furniture you could go and buy it back and go somewhere else and then - I've known 'em - do moonlight flits, take their beds and put 'em on the railways and all that kind of caper they've done
. And go off. Then when you got up next morning that house has been empty, oh, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468 somebody\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  gone. Moonlight flit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 But generally your mum would be able to manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes. I reckon her missed it a time or two same as anybody else 'cos - they all held
 rent, you know, they all had arrears in rent, nearly everybody and - they couldn't pay it, sometimes they wouldn't pay it, sometimes they couldn't pay it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you think he was a decent landlord, if you wanted repairs doing would you manage to get them done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Oh well they'd do 'em, 'cos I mean repairs didn't cost a lot in them days do they. I remember me mother putting sixteen pane of glass in on Sunday. Put her hand through 'em all. Or brick or something, and then we had to put an old bag up the 
window 'til the - and get a man across the road come put 'em in afore the rent man come next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Was she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468 mad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh - when her started. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468 Her and me father used to have a set-to.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 That's quite a thing, sixteen panes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well - yes, they were only little 'uns you know. Oh that was nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well as I say sometimes - one time we did like but - apart from that - I thought we were - you know, we wer
en't too bad you know, but there was - certain periods when he didn't have nothing you know
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So usually you had a fairly steady carry on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 I think we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 The livelihood went down because your dad was reliant on other people buying his stuff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. Then there was strike you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Was your dad ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
I can't remember him being ill. But he - he was - he was out of work on several occasion. Then he went in the Army when - he went in the war in 1914. He was gettin
g on then when he went in the war. Yes, and he was in the Militia, when he - in his early days you know, served a - a - long time in India.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you ever get help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes, sometime - one time we had
 to go on parish. We had - this - oh - brown bread they give you; two - they used to give you two loaves and so many shillings, not much you know then - 'course you could make your money go a good way then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So the amount you got depended on the amount of children you had in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes, I think so. They didn't give you a lot you know 'cos - as I say - shilling went a long time - a long way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 How would this brown bread and money be - paid out, did you ever have to go for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You had to go for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Sometimes I went. Sometimes I used to go for a woman over the was as is blind and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So they'd pay it out to children in fact?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well, we were older then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 How did you feel about this, can you remember how you felt about getting this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 No, because - I reckon they were used to it. Didn't take notice, they used to go and - just get it and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You didn't feel that this was a miserable thing to do, that you ought to have had a lot more than what you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Well everybody thought they ought to have a lot more didn't they I mean but - you had to be satisfied with what you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 When there was someone in the district who people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in wh
ich they showed it? In some areas if there were people who other more respectable folk - disapproved of, say there was a family they didn't like they'd go and make a great din outside the house and shout go away and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh yes, they'd shut you off. Yes, shut you off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Do you remember this happening to families then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 
Yes. Used to get our trust from shops then. Then some of 'em do 'em in and then go to another shop and have trust and that's how they carry on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 You mean they'd go and get things on credit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. Then they wouldn't pay 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 But can you remember when neighbours would sort of gang together in a street to get rid of somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Oh no. No, nothing like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14299416 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 So really it was a case of doing down people on the outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4343364 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468 Yes. As I say, if you wanted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468  to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  leave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12597533\charrsid15081468 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16325461\charrsid15081468  you could leave, you could get a house anywhere then.
\par }}